'''魔鬼学'''（{{lang-en|Demonology}}），指针对[[魔鬼|魔鬼]]・[[惡魔|惡魔]]・[[惡靈|惡靈]]或与其有关的信仰的系统的研究<ref>[http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/demonology "Demonology"] {{Wayback|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/demonology |date=20160304002812 }} at Dictionary.com Unabridged, (v 1.1) Random House, Inc., retrieved January 29 2007.</ref>。它是[[神学|神学]]的一个传统分支<ref>[http://biblia.com/theology/theology.htm Theology definition and kinds of Theology] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080218093459/http://biblia.com/theology/theology.htm |date=2008-02-18 }} at [[biblia.com|biblia.com]]</ref>，研究对象是一切超人的并且不是[[神|神]]的存在<ref name="hist">[http://www.history.com/encyclopedia.do?articleId=207375 "Demon"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071016201216/http://www.history.com/encyclopedia.do?articleId=207375 |date=2007-10-16 }} from Funk & Wagnalls ''New Encyclopedia'', © 2006 World Almanac Education Group, retrieved from [http://www.history.com/ history.com] {{Wayback|url=http://www.history.com/ |date=20111007094633 }}</ref>，广义上还包括那些不被或很少被人崇拜的善意的魔鬼。“demon”一词原本在[[荷马|荷马]]时代表示善意的靈體<ref name="DDD">van der Toorn, Becking, van der Horst (1999), ''Dictionary of Deities and Demons in The Bible'', Second Extensively Revised Edition, Entry: '''Demon''', pp. 235-240, William B. Eerdmans Publishing Company, ISBN 0-8028-2491-9</ref>，但經過時代變遷，在現代西方語言中却和邪恶联系起来。

魔鬼通常被看作一种灵体，可以是[[泛神论|泛神论]]中承认的两种灵体中的任何一种<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/01526a.htm Animism] {{Wayback|url=http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/01526a.htm |date=20170921175615 }} at [http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/index.html The Catholic Encyclopedia] {{Wayback|url=http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/index.html |date=20121018123012 }}</ref>。也就是说，魔鬼可以是人类或非人类可与肉体分离的[[灵魂|灵魂]]，亦或是从未进驻肉体的[[精神|精神]]。魔鬼学经常被使用的是它的负面内容，而实际上它并不像人们想象的那样总是与邪恶有关。[[阿拉伯|阿拉伯]]文化中的神怪就是一例。

魔鬼学的研究对象通常包括但不限于以下几种：
# [[犹太教|犹太教]]与[[基督教|基督教]]裡共有的[[堕落天使|堕落天使]]<ref name="DDD" />
# 被看做[[怪物|怪物]]或者[[妖精|妖精]]的人类灵魂<ref>[http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/demon Demon] {{Wayback|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/demon |date=20160303180646 }}, entry in the ''Online Etymology Dictionary'', © 2001 Douglas Harper, hosted at [http://dictionary.reference.com dictionary.com] {{Wayback|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/ |date=20150520140539 }}</ref>
# [[鬼|鬼]]或者其他[[邪灵|邪恶的亡灵]]<ref>[http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/ghost Ghost] {{Wayback|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/ghost |date=20160304204510 }}, entry in ''The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language'', Fourth Edition, Copyright © 2000, Houghton Mifflin Company, hosted at [http://dictionary.reference.com dictionary.com] {{Wayback|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/ |date=20150520140539 }}</ref>

